title: Cheesy Herby Biscuits
description:
At a big, holiday dinner, every dish has its role. The role of the protein is to act as the anchor, to center the plate 
and give it focus. The role of the veggie side dish is to provide a complementary taste and textural contrast to 
the protein. And of course, one of the most important roles is that of¿ well¿ the roll! Whether it's in the form 
of a dinner roll, mini baguette, or biscuit, the always-stalwart starch is a vital, hearty, gravy-sopping component 
to any holiday meal-and Trader Joe's Cheesy Herby Biscuits serve as a sensationally savory way to ensure 
this role is filled at your feast. 

Made with buttery, flaky dough, flavored with aromatic herbs like rosemary and thyme, and studded with 
shreds of rich Parmesan and Cheddar, our Cheesy Herby Biscuits arrive at our store frozen, so they're easy 
to grab ahead of time without worrying they'll get stale before the big day. They also taste best when baked 
directly from frozen (no need to proof!), in an un-preheated oven set to 375°F for about 30 minutes-the 
gradual heating helps the Biscuits retain their buttery, cheesy texture. Flaky, flavorful, and formidable, Trader 
Joe's Cheesy Herby Biscuits are a fantastic way to fill the roll role at Thanksgiving, the year-end holidays, or 
any other get-together where food is at the forefront. 

Cheesy Herby Biscuits
tags: ["Crack a Beer","Effortless Entertaining","Fall Faves","Family Style","Let's Bake!","Put An Egg On It"]

title: Spicy Farfalle Pasta with Italian Chicken Sausage
description:
Over the years, we've really grown our selection of Trader Joe's Italian-style pastas. In our freezers, you'll find a 
variety of noodle shapes and sauce options, from Spaghetti Carbonara [sku 75759] and Fettuccine Alfredo [sku 
41423] to Rigatoni Alla Contadina [sku 74185] and Penne Arrabbiata [sku 87813]. One thing these products all 
have in common-aside from being incredibly delicious values-is that they all serve more than one person 
(unless you're super hungry!). We decided it was time we created a single serving, frozen pasta dish, for when 
you're craving a hassle-free meal, but cooking just for one.

It starts with durum wheat Farfalle, a pasta shape not yet featured among our frozen pastas. These "bowties" 
are covered in a rich & spicy tomato sauce and paired with crumbles of savory Italian Chicken Sausage. To 
prepare, simply cook the Pasta from frozen according to the package instructions, plate it up, and enjoy! 

This Pasta dish is Spicy, but you're craving even more heat, try adding a spoonful of Italian Bomba Hot Pepper 
Sauce [sku 61934]. And if you want to add some fresh flair, we recommend some torn leaves of Organic Basil 
[sku 67343]. With or without these extras, you're in for a tasty meal... and we guarantee you won't have to worry 
about the leftovers. You'll find 12-ounce packages of Trader Joe's Farfalle Pasta with Italian Chicken Sausage 
in our freezers, every day.

Spicy Farfalle Pasta with Italian 
Chicken Sausage
tags: ["Alfresco Dining","Dinner Hack","Mouth On Fire","Pair With Wine"]

title: Cheesy Creamy Greens & Veggies
description:
"Can you please put the cheese back and get some greens instead?" asks the veggie lover of the veggie skeptic 
as they peruse their neighborhood Trader Joe's. "If loving cheese is wrong, I don't want to be right!" the 
skeptic cries, appalled by such a demand. Suddenly, out of the corners of their eyes, they see it: Cheesy Creamy 
Greens & Veggies. They share a glance. They smile. They realize this rich, Veggie-laden delight is the culinary 
peacemaker of their dreams. 

Cheesy Creamy Greens & Veggies start on a luxurious note with a butter, flour, and nutmeg roux. Onions, 
garlic, and black pepper lend aromatics and spice, while dried porcini mushrooms contribute deep umami. 
Then come provolone and mozzarella. Melty and salty-sweet, they expertly put the "cheese" in Cheesy Creamy 
Greens & Veggies. And, of course, cooked spinach finds cruciferous comrades in earthy kale and crisp Brussels 
sprouts. The result is a rich, textured, and Veggie-packed side dish or quick dinner that heats from frozen in 
eight minutes or less. Each box yields about two cups prepared, so there's plenty to satisfy even the pickiest of 
eaters. You'll find Cheesy Creamy Greens & Veggies only during the holiday season-pick up a box and bridge 
the veggie divide while supplies last!

Cheesy Creamy Greens & Veggies

title: Teriyaki Chicken Bowl
description:
Rich and juicy with savory-sweet flavor, it's no wonder that Trader Joe's BBQ Teriyaki Chicken [sku 74961] has 
been a customer favorite since 2004. It's a complete meal alongside white rice and steamed veggies, but on days 
you can't be bothered to take out the rice cooker and the steamer basket, Teriyaki Chicken Bowls make for an 
extra speedy and equally delicious alternative.

Much like the classic Japanese preparations of Teriyaki Chicken, we like to keep it simple. Establishing the 
foundation is chunks of dark Chicken thigh meat-think dense and juicy, with especially Chicken-y flavor. As 
for the sauce, ginger, garlic, and lime juice lend aromatic tang, while soy sauce, toasted sesame oil, and sugar 
contribute quintessentially sweet, umami-laden Teriyaki flavor. 

To make it a complete meal, we lay the Chicken over a bed of Calrose rice, alongside broccoli, carrots, and bok 
choy. It's an all-in-one lunch or dinner that heats from frozen in the microwave in about four minutes. If you've 
got a second to spare, garnish your Bowl with sesame seeds and sliced green onions, or a squirt of Sriracha 
Sauce [sku 50828] for a spicy kick. 

Teriyaki Chicken Bowl

title: Roti with Thai Red Curry
description:
Roti canai is a flatbread and curry dish that originated in India in the 1800s. In the decades after its inception, 
Southeast Asian countries like Brunei, Indonesia, Malaysia, Singapore, and Thailand developed their own 
variations. And now, Trader Joe's takes a spin on this classic combination with our Roti with Thai Red Curry.

You'll find three Roti in each box. They're made with wheat flour, sea salt, and rice bran oil & shortening for 
layered, flaky flatbreads. For the Red Curry, we mix together rich coconut milk with a considerably spicy Red 
Curry paste containing traditional Thai seasonings like lemongrass, birds eye chiles, spur chiles, Thai basil, 
and galangal (a cooling, pine-like spice, if you're unfamiliar). We finish things off with a light-yet-filling mix of 
green eggplant, cabbage, and potatoes. We'd say this vegan duo is ro-teeming with bright, complex flavors and 
wonderfully complementary textures. 

To prepare it, warm the Roti on a skillet, in the oven, or in the air fryer according to package directions. Then, 
thaw the Curry packet in warm water for 1-2 minutes before heating through in the microwave or on the stove. 
To eat it, tear off pieces of the Roti and use them to scoop up the Curry, or pour the Curry on top of the Roti. 
Enjoy as a quick and filling snack, or make it a flavorful dinner alongside a glass of zesty Emma Reichart Dry 
Riesling [sku 61437] or a can of light Simpler Times Lager [sku 62590].

Roti with Thai Red Curry
tags: ["Crack a Beer","Dinner Hack","Feeling Adventurous","In Lieu of Pizza","Mouth On Fire"]

title: Mushroom Risotto
description:
Risotto comes from the Italian word "riso", which means "rice" in English. Now, you can't talk about risotto 
without mentioning its main ingredient, which is rice of course. Since the introduction of the grain, rice 
farming has been a major part of life for many Italian families. 

Trader Joe's Mushroom Risotto is imported from Italy and made by one of the best. The dish is authentic, 
creamy, savory, and extremely delicious! The "riso" is parcooked and combined with cream, slices of mushroom, 
onion, garlic, and extra Porcini mushroom seasoning. For a complete Italian dinner, light some candles, dim 
the lights and offer Trader Joe's Mushroom Risotto with a side of Focaccia Bread [sku 64435] and Balsamic 
Vinegar [sku 58036] or Italian President's Reserve [sku 30090] for dipping. Make the Risotto the star on the 
table as a main entree with your favorite protein and Caesar Salad [sku 05161]. 

Make your way to the freezers to enjoy this 16-ounce taste of Italy. 

 *Please check QIL to confirm current pricing.

Mushroom Risotto

title: Coffee Panna Cotta
description:
Crème caramel, flan, rožata, purin, pudin karamel-the many variations of caramel-covered custard have 
many names around the world. Here at Trader Joe's, our creamy, coffee-imbued version goes by Coffee Panna 
Cotta, and is available in our refrigerated section for a limited time. 

Our Panna Cotta (Italian for "cooked cream") is made for us in Texas by a Portugese company that specializes in 
the dessert. Our supplier combines the Panna Cotta starting lineup of cream, milk, and sugar with a generous 
amount of Coffee powder for intense Coffee flavor. While many Panna Cottas are gelatinous in texture, ours is 
decidedly creamy and more texturally akin to flan. Caramelized syrup sits in the bottom of the two individual 
foil cups in each package, finishing off the Panna Cotta with rich and toasty sweetness. 

To serve, peel back the lid, carefully run a knife around the perimeter of the Panna Cotta, flip it upside down 
onto a plate, and enjoy. Serve it with a glass of Chocolate Whole Milk [sku 61673] for a mocha-inspired dessert. 
Or, pay homage to this Panna Cotta's Portugese roots by pairing it with luscious and toasty Morgado Tawny 
Port [sku 47763]. 

Coffee Panna Cotta

title: Savory Squash Pastry Bites
description:
Entertaining guests? How about just wondering what's for dinner? Our newest frozen appetizer answers both 
questions with fanciful fall flair. Introducing Trader Joe's Savory Squash Pastry Bites!

First things first-unwrap the Pastry Bites and place them on a baking sheet. After about 12 minutes in a 
400°F oven (or half that time in an air fryer), you'll be rewarded with a buttery Pastry crust teeming with a 
pumpkin & butternut Squash-forward filling, along with a Savory symphony of flavors courtesy of not one, but 
four different cheeses-namely, creamy mascarpone and ricotta, tangy feta, and pleasantly sharp Parmesan. 
Finished with chopped chives, these Pastry Bites lend an air of elegance to an appetizer platter or buffet spread 
for a harvest fête (don't forget the bubbly!), and are equally at home on a weeknight dinner plate alongside a 
crisp green salad topped with crumbled White Stilton® Cheese with Apple & Pear [sku 79157]. 

While these Savory Squash Pastry Bites may look upscale, their price is, happily, not! You'll find them in the 
freezers at your neighborhood Trader Joe's, for a limited time. 

Savory Squash Pastry Bites

title: Gluten Free Cheese Pizza
description:
Trader Joe's sells Gluten Free Pizza Dough [sku 64663] if you're in the mood to make a pie from scratch. But if 
you're looking for a ready-to-bake, gluten free solution, look no further than Trader Joe's Gluten Free Cheese 
Pizza with a Cauliflower Crust. 

You've seen this kind of pie before, even in our freezers, so we can't exactly claim it's revolutionary. We can 
say that the delicious Gluten Free crust (first ingredient: Cauliflower) develops a nice crispness in just 10-12 
minutes in the oven. It handily delivers our tangy tomato sauce, and melty mozzarella & provolone cheeses 
right to your mouth. 

Perhaps what's most impressive about this Gluten Free Cheese Pizza is the possibilities. While we've engineered 
this pie to be enjoyable just as it is, it's also a blank canvas for your own pizza creativity. And with a Trader Joe's 
store full of toppings, it's safe to say, the possibilities are endless! 

Gluten Free Cheese Pizza with a 
Cauliflower Crust
tags: ["Alfresco Dining","Crack a Beer","Dinner Hack","Family Style","Game Night","Rain or Shine"]

title: Coffee Mochi
description:
Something's brewing in the Trader Joe's Freezer section. They're bite-sized, handheld, and elliptically shaped. 
They've got a chewy exterior and lush ice cream center. They taste like your morning cup of joe. Why, they're 
Coffee Mochi, here for a limited time!

Unlike other Mochi on the market made with synthetically derived flavors and high fructose corn syrup, 
the frozen filling in Trader Joe's Coffee Mochi gets its bold Coffee flavor and color from Coffee itself, and 
possesses a balanced sweetness thanks to real cane sugar. A hint of cocoa gives the sweet, chewy rice flour 
dough its rich brown hue, and adds a touch of chocolate on the palate to round out the robust Coffee notes. 

Coffee Mochi make for a delightful handheld pick-me-up that's best enjoyed after thawing for 3-4 minutes. 
That may seem like a long time, but you'll be hard pressed to eat just one anyway, so why not assemble a variety 
platter of these gluten free treats while you're at it? Reach for Vanilla [sku 64500], Strawberry [64499], and 
Green Tea [sku 64669] for a sweet, fruity, and aromatic Mochi mix! 

Coffee Mochi

title: Chicken Sausage Breakfast Bowl
description:
Have you ever been bowling for breakfast? It's quick, easy, and quite convenient-especially if you're talking 
about Trader Joe's Chicken Sausage Breakfast Bowl. This tasty combination of fluffy scrambled eggs, pieces of 
herb-seasoned Chicken Sausage, and shredded Cheddar cheese is already fully cooked and goes from freezer 
to table in just 2-3 microwave minutes. But maybe you don't have much time for the table part? That's ok, since 
this Chicken Sausage Breakfast Bowl is eminently portable and easy to enjoy almost anywhere, as long as you 
have a fork. (Although, if you tuck the Bowl contents into a TJ's tortilla, that fork won't even be necessary!)

When you do have more time, Trader Joe's Chicken Sausage Breakfast Bowl is easy to personalize. Add in 
some TJ's Shredded Hash Browns [sku 96969]. Garnish with some Organic Cilantro [sku 45683] and slices of 
avocado. Spice it up with a drizzle of Crunchy Chili Onion [sku 62480], or Chunky Garlic & Jalapeño hot Sauce 
[sku 74550]. You'll find seven-ounce Chicken Sausage Breakfast Bowls in our freezers, every day. Get one for 
tomorrow's breakfast, plus a spare for whenever the mood strikes!

Chicken Sausage Breakfast Bowl

title: Organic Silver Dollar Pancakes
description:
It's true what the say: breakfast really is the most important meal of the day. But that doesn't mean it has to be 
the most labor-intensive. In fact, with Trader Joe's Organic Silver Dollar Pancakes, the only thing separating 
you from a stack of scrumptious, home-style, bite-sized Pancakes is a minute or two in the microwave. That 
means you have all the more time to focus on what might be the most important part of such an important 
meal: what, exactly, you'll choose to top them with!

With their subtly savory, from-scratch taste, our Organic Silver Dollar Pancakes are a natural fit with our 
Organic Vermont Maple Syrup [sku 66402] or Organic Maple Agave Syrup Blend [sku 99105]. That's hardly 
where we'd stop, however: hot from the microwave, these Organic Pancakes are especially delicious with a pat 
of melty butter, a cool dollop of whipped cream (or Coconut Whipped Topping [sku 58113], for that matter), or 
even a scoop of ice cream. And we simply adore them with sliced strawberries, sweet fruit preserves, or a nice 
spread of Speculoos Cookie Butter [sku 96761].

Organic Silver Dollar Pancakes

title: Ginger Shrimp Lo Mein
description:
The classic Chinese-American restaurant menu has nearly too many hits to name. Wonton soup? An absolute 
winner. Chow mein? A total chart-topper. Fried rice? A certified phenom. And for the newest addition to our 
frozen entrée assortment, we're drawing inspiration from one of the greatest hits of them all: lo mein. Made for 
us by a longtime supplier in Thailand who specializes in succulent shrimp dishes, Trader Joe's Ginger Shrimp 
Lo Mein offers all the same rich aromatics, savory flavors, and tantalizingly toothsome textures that made lo 
mein such a legend in the first place.

Inside each package of Trader Joe's Ginger Shrimp Lo Mein, you'll find a pack of wheat noodles, a medley of 
veggies including white cabbage and bell peppers, and a pouch of raw shrimp in a savory ginger-shiitake sauce. 
All it takes is a few minutes of sautéeing in a skillet for these ingredients to go from frozen to steamy, fragrant, 
and ready to eat. Ginger Shrimp Lo Mein can be enjoyed on its own as an entrée for one or two, or combined 
with other dishes as part of a family-style feast: we particularly like pairing it with some garlicky, stir-fried Baby 
Broccoli [sku 47468], and a plate of steamed Chicken Gyoza Potstickers [sku 03663].

Ginger Shrimp Lo Mein

title: Roasted Corn
description:
Trader Joe's Roasted Corn is grown in the sunny valleys of Washington State and harvested at the peak of 
ripeness. It's then roasted over an open flame, adding a smoky dimension to the corn's natural sweetness. After 
roasting, the corn is individually quick frozen to ensure freshness and allow you to use what you like now and 
save the rest for another time. 

If you're looking for a versatile side dish, our Roasted Corn may just fit the bill. The corn is great by itself and 
fits great with a variety of other combinations, especially in ethnic dishes. Once cooked, toss the amount of 
Corn you would like to use for a Mexican-style salad with Organic Black Beans [sku 50262], quinoa, cilantro, 
topped with sweet peppers, onions, avocado and creamy, Cilantro Dressing [sku 36420] with crumbled cotija 
cheese. The Corn makes for a delicious Elote in a cup, also known as Esquites. Just like you would on a corn on 
the cob, add Real Mayonnaise [sku 01482], grated Cotija Cheese [sku 65005], chili powder, and a Trader Joe's 
touch with our crushed Elote Chips [sku 60564]. You'll find each 16-ounce bag of Trader Joe's Roasted Corn 
in our freezers. 

 *Please check QIL to confirm current 

Roasted Corn

title: Steamed Vegetable Soup Dumplings
description:
From the moment they were introduced, our Steamed Chicken Soup Dumplings [sku 54988] and Steamed 
Pork & Ginger Soup Dumplings [sku 65259] became instant sensations among our customers. Inspired by the 
winsome dim sum tradition of Chinese xiao long bao, these aromatic and savory, soup-filled dumplings are 
such a darling, in fact, that we've received countless requests to make a vegan version, as well. After trying a few 
variations, our tasting panel found that a mix of jackfruit, carrot, cabbage, spinach, and ginger for the filling, 
along with a hearty, aromatic broth (made with vegan-friendly agar-agar, rather than gelatin) made for a truly 
captivating combination-and thus, Trader Joe's Steamed Vegetable Soup Dumplings were born!

Just like our Pork and Chicken variations, our Steamed Vegetable Soup Dumplings can be made in a matter 
of minutes in the microwave or steamer on your stovetop. Also like their predecessors, once heated through, 
the soup inside of them does become quite hot-we recommend serving them in a deep spoon, carefully 
puncturing the top of the side of the dumpling with your teeth or some chopsticks, then letting the soup seep 
into the spoon to cool down until it's ready to slurp. We also heartily recommend enjoying them with a bit of 
Reduced Sodium Soy Sauce [sku 26426] and Crunchy Chili Onion [sku 62480] for an even more satisfying Soup 
Dumpling experience. 

Steamed Vegetable Soup Dumplings
tags: ["Chance of Rain","Cold Front","Dinner Hack","Rain or Shine"]

title: Bubble Waffles
description:
If you're a fan of bubble tea beverages (a.k.a. boba), then chances are you've seen Bubble Waffles sold right 
along with them. Also known as gai daan zai in Cantonese, they first appeared on the Hong Kong street-food 
scene way back in the 1950s. Later nicknamed "Bubble Waffles," at least in part for their uncanny resemblance 
to actual bubble wrap, they've been a standby in cafés, sidewalk stalls, and home kitchens ever since... and now, 
in the freezers at your neighborhood Trader Joe's, too! (We can sense your bubbling joy from here!)

Made with coconut milk, wheat flour, cane sugar, rice bran shortening, and vanilla bean paste, our vegan 
Trader Joe's Bubble Waffles are fluffy yet chewy, sweet yet savory, and simple yet versatile. Heat them from 
frozen in your air fryer, toaster oven, or microwave, and their crispy edges and mochi-like middles are ready 
to be topped with everything from fresh fruit & whipped cream, to Cookie Butter [sku 96761] & bananas, to 
French Vanilla Ice Cream [sku 78576] & All Occasion Sprinkle [sku 77039]. You can even top them with savory 
fare, like shredded Le Gruyère Cheese [sku 97621] and chopped leeks, or fried eggs and Sriracha Sauce [sku 
50828]. Really, the sky's the limit here-don't let anything burst your Bubbles! Except for you, when you're 
eating them, of course.

Bubble Waffles
tags: ["Brunch All Day","Family Style","Gild The Lily","Rain or Shine","The \"X\" Factor"]

title: Tropical Green Tea Instant Boba Kit
description:
Two summers back, we brought the proverbial boba shop home with the introduction of our everyday Instant 
Boba Kit [sku 73998], and it's remained a hot ticket in our freezers ever since. So much so, in fact, that when 
approached by a Taiwanese supplier with an opportunity to offer a limited-time, more Tropical-tasting Boba 
Kit, we lept at the chance! You'll be leaping, too, as soon as you get your hands on a Trader Joe's Tropical 
Green Tea Instant Boba Kit.

For about the same price you'd pay for a single boba drink at a café, our Tropical Green Tea Boba Kit contains 
four pouches of vegan, gluten-free, tapioca pearls in a sweet, passion fruit & mango-flavored green tea syrup, 
plus four wide-gauge paper straws to help you capture some of said pearls in every sip. The Boba pearls only 
take a minute in the microwave to heat up; from there, it's just a matter of placing them into the bottom of  a 
glass, adding ice, and pouring in your beverage of choice, like milk, green tea, coconut beverage, or even just 
cold water-anything goes! Then sit back, take a sip, and enjoy the sweet, refreshing, texturally satisfying ride.

Tropical Green Tea Instant Boba Kit

title: Panzerotti Pizza Bites
description:
What look like mini calzones, taste like cheese pizza, and eat like some of the tastiest hors d'oeuvres around? New 
Trader Joe's Panzerotti Pizza Bites, that's what! Made for us in Southern Italy by a supplier who specializes in 
this very appetizer, these two-to-three-bite-sized, lightly fried Pizza pockets take the concept of "after-school 
pizza rolls" and elevates it to flavorful new heights!

Picture this: each Trader Joe's Panzerotti Pizza Bite begins with a pleasantly chewy, half-moon-shaped pouch 
of pizza dough, which gets subsequently stuffed with a melty, mozzarella cheese blend and bold Italian tomato 
sauce, then quick-fried in vegetable oil. Simple? Yes. Simply irresistable? Also yes. Just heat them from frozen 
(we're talking 12 minutes in a conventional oven, 8-10 minutes in an air fryer, or 1-2 minutes in a microwave 
here, folks-minimal effort), and you've got one delicious appetizer or snack on your hands... or rather, you've 
got several delicious Panzerotti Pizza Bites in your hands!  

Panzerotti Pizza Bites
tags: ["Alfresco Dining","Crack a Beer","Family Style","Finger Food","Game Night","Midday Snacks"]

title: Pad See Ew
description:
An indisputable icon of Thai restaurant menus and street food stalls the world over, pad see ew translates 
to "fried with soy sauce," and was likely popularized within Thailand by Chinese immigrants in the early 
20th century. A bit like a localized, Thai-cuisine-informed variation of chow fun (which was likely a direct 
inspiration), pad see ew is traditionally made with wide, flat rice noodles, which are fried in a wok with various 
veggies and garlic before being finished with a splash of light and dark soy sauce to give it a bold, savory, and 
umami-rich flavor. And that's the same, time-tested technique that our supplier in Thailand uses when making 
Trader Joe's Pad See Ew, a rich, flavorful, and totally vegan version of this classic dish that's now available in 
our freezers.

After mere minutes in the microwave, Trader Joe's Pad See Ew makes an excellent work lunch, dinner entrée, 
or savory side dish. Every bite expresses a delightful depth of flavor, as well as a remarkable range of textures, 
from the tender chewiness of the noodles, to the snap of the carrots and Chinese broccoli, to the soft, tooth-
sink-ability of the tofu chunks and tofu sheets. We recommend serving it alongside our (also vegan) Thai Green 
Curry [sku 70789], some fluffy jasmine rice, and a plate of stir-fried Baby Bok Choy [sku 98253].

Pad See Ew

title: Mango Cream Bars
description:
Creamy, fruity, frozen bars are so fun and yummy for summer. This season, our customers have already enjoyed 
TJ's Tangerine Cream Bars [sku 69861] and TJ's Blueberry Dream Bars [sku 74250]. Normally, Trader Joe's 
Mango & Cream Bars [sku 92373] (available year-round) would have been part of this polar produce party-
except our Australian supplier announced earlier this year that they were unable to keep up, after more than a 
dozen years of meeting our mango bar demand. Without skipping a beat we sought a new supplier, this time, 
closer to home. We also took the opportunity to make some minor improvements before presenting our latest 
Mango Cream Bars.

Flavor-wise, these are similar to the previous iteration-a combination of creamy vanilla and sweet-tart mango. 
What sticks out here as different is... the stick. (Previous version was sans stick.) And rather than the flavors 
existing side-by-side, in this version, the creamy vanilla ice cream is entirely surrounded by sweet, fruity mango 
sorbet. It's the same format as our Tangerine Cream Bars, only with Mango.

You might also find that Trader Joe's Mango Cream Bars are a bit richer overall. That's because the first 
ingredient is vanilla ice cream (it was water in the original version). Plus, the fruity part is made with purée of 
both Magdalena and Alphonso mango varieties, delivering a tart & sweet, totally tropical taste!

Mango Cream Bars

title: Crispy Battered Calamari
description:
There's nothing like hitting the bar at happy hour and enjoying some fried appetizers and discounted drinks 
with friends, although... hitting the home "bar" with some appetizers from TJ's has its perks. Besides not 
needing to leave your house, and saving money on tips, you also get the opportunity to enjoy tasty appetizers 
from our freezers, like Trader Joe's Crispy Battered Calamari.

We worked with seafood specialists in Italy to develop our own version of the classic Italian Anelli alla 
Romana ("Roman Rings"). Our Calamari is made with squid rings and tentacles that are lightly battered with 
a combination of wheat flour, rice semolina, and baking soda. This helps develop a Crispy crunch during 
cooking in your conventional oven or air fryer. And they're seasoned with salt, black pepper, garlic, onion, and 
chili pepper; just the right amount of flavor to enjoy as-is, or with a simple squeeze of fresh lemon juice. 

Of course, dipping these Crispy Battered squid into your favorite TJ's sauce (we have so many!) adds yet 
another layer of deliciousness. You'll find 16-ounce packages of Trader Joe's Crispy Battered Calamari every 
day in our freezers. Keep some in your freezer, for the next time you and your friends decide to have a happy 
hour at home.

Crispy Battered Calamari

title: Mini Shrimp Bao
description:
Of all the various carbs and starches that the world's cuisines have produced, we have to admit that we have a 
true soft spot for the bao bun-and for its soft and pillowy texture, in particular. That, combined with its mild, 
delicately savory, and just a touch sweet flavor, makes the bao bun an especially compelling conveyance for 
hearty proteins and aromatic sauces, as Trader Joe's Mini Shrimp Bao rather deliciously demonstrate. Made 
for us by an expert supplier in Vietnam, each box contains eight miniature, clamshell-style Bao laden with a 
well-seasoned shrimp patty, as well as a sweet and sticky lemongrass, lime, and chili sauce for dipping.

Excellent as an appetizer, hors d'oeuvre, or side dish, Trader Joe's Mini Shrimp Bao offer a marvelous medley of 
complementary flavors and textures in every bite. Individually, each Bao takes less than a minute to microwave, 
and when prepped together, only a few minutes in the steamer before they're tender, tasty, and ready to serve. 
They can be enjoyed as they are, right out of the box, or, if you prefer, dressed to your liking; we're partial to 
garnishing each Bao with quick-pickled cucumber ribbons, shredded carrots, and freshly torn cilantro leaves.

Mini Shrimp Bao

title: Seafood Boil
description:
In our estimation, nothing represents the very best aspects of Cajun cuisine better than a classic, Louisiana-
style seafood boil. There's the remarkable range of flavors, the ingenuity of ingredients, and, of course, the 
overall emphasis on community-what else can bring people together like a big batch of fiery-hot shellfish, 
after all? In honor of this storied (not to mention well-spiced) tradition, we're bringing in Trader Joe's Seafood 
Boil to our freezers. Each box contains a bag of shrimp, tilapia, clams, and andouille sausage, along with hearty 
corn on the cob and miniature potatoes, all pre-seasoned with a lip-smackingly spicy garlic butter sauce. Ça 
c'est bon, non?

Once home, your Trader Joe's Seafood Boil can be conveniently prepped by either boiling it all in-bag, or 
by placing the contents of the bag in a sauce pan and heating until cooked through. Either way, in about 20-
25 minutes, you'll have a spicy, buttery, Cajun-style seafood and veggie medley ready to be served. It makes 
an excellent and practically effortless weeknight dinner option, especially considering each bag contains two 
hearty servings. We recommend pairing your Seafood Boil with an Everyday Butter Lettuce Salad [sku 74072] 
and some white rice or crusty bread to soak up as much of that garlicky, buttery sauce as you can. 

Seafood Boil

title: Organic Freezer Pops
description:
Remember back when you were a kid, and one of the coolest ways to cool down was to grab an ice-cold freezer 
pop? As it turns out, that's still one of the coolest ways to cool down, which is why we're bringing Trader Joe's 
Organic Freezer Pops to our shelves! Just like the classic, fruity freezer pops you grew up with, ours arrive at 
the store in a shelf-stable package and only need to be frozen overnight before they're ready to enjoy. Unlike 
those freezer pops of the past, however, ours are certified Organic and contain 100% juice!

Inside each package, you'll find ten Pops in three fantastic flavors: three sweet and citric Orange Pops, three 
rich and refreshing Berry Pops, and four tart and tangy Cherry Limeade Pops. An excellent anytime sweet treat 
for kids and adults alike, Trader Joe's Organic Freezer Pops make an especially nice bit of refreshment for 
enjoying after school, sports practices, and other outdoor activities. Once you take them home, we recommend 
giving them a quick shake before freezing-since they're made with real fruit juice concentrates, this will help 
reduce any natural separation that may occur as the juices inside each Pop settle. 

Organic Freezer Pops

title: Mango Mochi
description:
With the perennial popularity of our ice cream Mochi and all things Mango (see TJ's Soft & Juicy Mango [sku 
98741], TJ's Mango Cream Bars [sku 74869], et al.), one might argue that the development of Trader Joe's 
Mango Mochi was¿ well, inevitable. And you wouldn't be wrong-our Buyer had Mango on her mind from 
the moment she was charged with the task of creating our next, limited-edition Mochi flavor.

Like our everyday Mochi options (Vanilla [sku 64500], Green Tea [sku 64669], & Strawberry [sku 64499]), 
Trader Joe's Mango Mochi are essentially one-or-two-bite-sized scoops of sweet-tart Mango ice cream, 
surrounded by soft, chewy Mochi  rice wrappers. While these frozen delicacies might be small, they pack a 
whole lot of mango flavor. Heck, the ice cream itself contains more than 20% alphonso mango purée-talk 
about tropical treats!

Mango Mochi

title: Lemon Ginger Cheesecake
description:
Just between us, dear reader: you work hard. You do! You clearly care about the kind of food you eat and feed 
to your loved ones. If you don't mind us saying so, you deserve something sweet and delicious. Honestly, you 
deserve to treat yourself to a Trader Joe's Lemon Ginger Cheesecake. With everything you do, you should 
absolutely take the time to savor every bite of this Cheesecake's tantalizingly tart cream cheese base, flavored 
with lemon curd and actual bits of lemon peel, as well as its dense, crumbly, gingersnap crust. 

Lemon Ginger Cheesecake is an excellent dessert option for bringing along to cookouts, serving to friends 
at the end of weekend brunches, or simply enjoying as an anytime reward for being the kind of dedicated, 
determined person you are. "Now, now," you might be saying, "surely, such a rich and decadent Cheesecake 
comes with an equally extravagant price tag." While that's an utterly understandable sentiment, each seven-
inch-diameter, 30-ounce Trader Joe's Lemon Ginger Cheesecake sells for about the same price you'd pay - or 
less! - for a single slice of cheesecake at a bakery or restaurant, making it an eminently affordable indulgence. 
Stop by your Trader Joe's freezer section to pick one up while supplies last. You deserve it!

Lemon Ginger Cheesecake

title: Super Strawberry Sorbet
description:
We didn't just name our brand-new sorbet flavor "Super Strawberry Sorbet," for the alliteration. (Although, 
it is fun to say.) In fact, we called it super because we think that's the best word to describe Trader Joe's latest, 
fruity, frozen treat! Even beyond the "super-fruit" status of strawberries, this Sorbet has other superb qualities 
going for it. Our supplier in Thailand starts with locally harvested strawberries that have a balanced, sweet & tart 
flavor, which translates sensationally when blended with water & cane sugar to form the smooth Sorbet base. 
Then, they add Strawberry pieces to amp up the texture and augment the Super Strawberry flavor. 

We're confident that anyone who gets their hands on (and their spoons in) Trader Joe's Super Strawberry 
Sorbet is going to love it. In particular, those who avoid animal products will definitely be assigning superlatives 
to this vegan dessert. But you can't love it if you never try it... so grab a pint from our freezers while supplies last! 

Super Strawberry Sorbet

title: Salsa Verde Chicken Enchiladas
description:
Our Crew works hard every day so that anyone who walks into their neighborhood Trader Joe's can say, "This 
is not your average grocery store!" 'Not your average' means we're committed to providing outstanding value 
in the form of the best quality products at the best everyday prices. And this approach extends across all the 
products in our stores, including Trader Joe's Not Your Average Salsa Verde Chicken Enchiladas.

The qualities that make these Enchiladas beyond average are found in every aspect of their construction. 
Tender, brothy, dark-chicken meat has been shredded and tucked into two corn tortillas in ample quantities. 
Side-by-side, the Chicken Enchiladas are generously covered with a flavorful Salsa Verde that's green with 
tomatillos, poblano chilis, and jalapeño peppers. The final tasty touch is a sprinkling of diced peppers and 
some melty (once heated) mozzarella. Speaking of heating, about the only thing one could say is average about 
these Enchiladas is the fact that you conveniently cook them in either a microwave or a conventional oven.

But back to the extraordinary: each 16.5-ounce package (that's over a pound!) of Trader Joe's Not Your Average 
Salsa Verde Chicken Enchiladas is available on any average day in our stores. You'll find them in our freezers. 

Not Your Average Salsa Verde 
Chicken Enchiladas
tags: ["Crack a Beer","Dinner Hack","In Lieu of Pizza","Time-pressed"]

title: Meatless Meatballs
description:
Can you have meatballs without meat? Trader Joe's Meatless Meatballs answer with a resounding (and 
delicious) yes! So, if it's not meat, what is it? We're glad you asked. These Meatless Meatballs are expertly 
crafted from textured soy protein (TSP)-which is what remains after extracting the oil from soybeans. It's 
"textured" because it has the appearance & mouthfeel of meat. It's "protein" because it naturally contains a 
notable amount of protein-13g of protein per 4-Meatball serving.

Our Meatless Meatballs are also delicious, since the TSP is seasoned like the best Italian-style meatballs, using 
a combination of onions, garlic powder, parsley, basil, sea salt, and black pepper-plus mushroom powder, for 
an umami-boost. The seasoned soy protein is then formed into couple-bite sized rounds, which are flash frozen 
so they're at-the-ready whenever the urge for Meatballs hits. And when it does hit, you can quickly heat these  
kosher, vegan, Meatless morsels using a variety of convenient methods (detailed on the package). In a matter 
of just 4 to 14 minutes-depending on your approach-you'll have savory, tender, Meatless Meatballs that 
complement your pasta, or make a great sandwich stuffer.

Meatless Meatballs
tags: ["Alfresco Dining","Crack a Beer","Dinner Hack","Fry It Up","Make It Meatless","Pair With Wine"]

title: Japanese Soufflé Cheesecakes
description:
Sitting somewhere at the intersection of light & airy and rich & creamy (an intersection that happens to 
look a whole lot like the freezer case at your neighborhood Trader Joe's), new Trader Joe's Japanese Soufflé 
Cheesecakes present a study in contrasts. Made with sweetened condensed milk and cream cheese, they 
straddle the line between light-as-air soufflés and moist, toothsome cheesecakes-and oh, what a delicious 
line it is.

Made for us in Japan, where simple, single-serve cakes like these are ubiquitous in cafes and corner stores, TJ's 
Soufflé Cheesecakes are an easy, no-mess dessert option for evenings (or afternoons) when being tethered to 
an oven isn't on the menu. Simply remove these cute, crustless cakes from their packaging when you get home 
from work, school, or carpool duty, thaw them for about 3 hours in the refrigerator, and dessert is served! Or, 
if you're feeling fancy, top them with a few fresh strawberry slices, a scoop of TJ's Ube Ice Cream [sku 61854], 
or a spoonful of TJ's Mandarin Oranges in Light Syrup [sku 20609] and whipped cream. 

Japanese Soufflé Cheesecakes

title: Jumeokbap
description:
You've really got to hand it to jumeokbap. From the Korean "jumeok" (fist) and "bap" (rice), food historians 
estimate that this hearty, handheld dish has likely been a staple of Korean cuisine for thousands of years. Now a 
rising star in the global street food scene, jumeokbap can be made with any number of fillings and seasonings, 
and can be enjoyed in all manner of contexts: as a quick, on-the-go bite, as a side with a larger meal, or as a 
miniature meal all its own. Made for us by a supplier in the Republic of Korea, Trader Joe's Jumeokbap are 
flavored with a mix of plant-based bulgogi and savory-seasoned vegetables, and take only about a minute in 
the microwave to go from frozen to soft, steamy, and ready-to-eat.

Traditionally, jumeokbap are spherical, reflecting the shape of a closed fist. Trader Joe's Jumeokbap are a little 
more pyramidal, making them a kind of vegan mashup of jumeokbap and Japanese onigiri. We recommend 
them as a hearty snack when you're feeling peckish between meals, and we especially recommend serving them 
with a sauce for dipping. Try pairing a Jumeokbap or two with a bit of our Gyoza Dipping Sauce [sku 84399], 
or a little mayo mixed with TJ's Sriracha [sku 50828] or Gochujang Paste [sku 73246].

Jumeokbap
tags: ["Crack a Beer","Dinner Hack","Feeling Adventurous","In Lieu of Pizza"]

title: Shrimp Scampi
description:
Shrimp, garlic, butter, lemon, and white wine. The ingredients to a classic shrimp scampi feel so made for one 
another, so iconic in their expression of flavor when combined, that it's somewhat shocking to realize that the 
dish is only about a century old. In fact, when it was invented in Italy during the 1920s, it was simply known 
as "scampi," and featured langoustine lobster, rather than shrimp. As delicious as that certainly was, we're glad 
to be living in the era of the modern shrimp scampi we all know and love-an era which now includes the 
consummately convenient and phenomenally flavorful Trader Joe's Shrimp Scampi, available in our freezers.

Made with a recipe inspired by this staple of Italian-American cuisine, each package is made with shelled, 
deveined, tail-off shrimp in a rich, flavorful, and enchantingly aromatic sauce made with garlic, butter, white 
wine, lemon juice, and a bit of grated Romano cheese for an extra touch of umami oomph. It cooks quickly and 
easily on the stovetop or in the oven, after which it can be served with pasta, rice, crusty bread, or entirely on its 
own. We like our Shrimp Scampi as a simple, satisfying, no-fuss entrée for a busy weeknight dinner, especially 
when paired with a side of roasted broccoli, a baked potato, and a crisp and fruity white wine-something like 
our subtly sparkly Espiral Vinho Verde [sku 97395], for example.

Shrimp Scampi

title: Kimbap
description:
Known in Korea as gimbap, from gim for "seaweed" and bap for "cooked rice," kimbap is similar to-but 
decidedly distinct from-a mega-sized maki sushi roll. Whereas maki is typically made with vinegar-seasoned 
rice and focuses on one filling (like a single variety of vegetable or fish), kimbap is made with sesame oil-seasoned 
rice, and can contain all kinds of combinations of savory fillings. Trader Joe's Kimbap, for example, takes a 
veggie-forward approach. Our supplier, a kimbap expert in the Republic of Korea, arranges an assortment of 
sauteed greens, crunchy root vegetables, and crisp pickles around a base of braised tofu, wraps it all in a layer 
of rice and seaweed, then slices it into two-or-three-bite-sized rounds.

When viewed in cross section, our conveniently quick-cooking Kimbap resembles a marvelous, multi-flavored 
mosaic. After cooking from frozen for a mere two minutes in the microwave, it can be enjoyed hot or chilled, 
served as an entrée, side, or snack. While it's flavorful enough to hold its own as a dish, it also accessorizes well 
with a bit of Sriracha [sku 50828], Gochujang Sauce [sku 74565], or Reduced Sodium Soy Sauce [sku 26426]. For 
an even more satisfying textural dimension, we recommend giving each piece a quick pan-fry: two minutes in 
hot oil per side ought to do the trick.

Kimbap
tags: ["Alfresco Dining","Crack a Beer","In Lieu of Pizza","Rain or Shine","The \"X\" Factor"]

title: Mini Chocolate Chip Croissant Swirls
description:
The word croissant is French for "crescent," describing the classic, moon-sliver shape of these buttery, baked 
delights. But croissants can come in many shapes, as evidenced by Trader Joe's Mini Chocolate Chip Croissant 
Swirls.

In these Mini Croissants, the crescent is superseded by the Swirl. Our French bakery supplier starts with 
familiar croissant construction, using layers upon layers of thin, wheat-flour dough, alternating with layers 
of cultured butter. The dough is then rolled into long cylinders, which are cut into discs resembling spiral 
galaxies, if you will. And a generous sprinkling of semi-sweet Chocolate Chips are the stars of these systems. 

Our Ready-to-Bake Mini Croissant Swirls go directly from freezer to oven; no proofing required. Simply 
allow the frozen Swirls to rest at room temperature on a parchment-lined baking sheet for as long as it takes to 
pre-heat your oven to 350°F, pop them in, and 25-30 minutes later you'll be over the moon for golden brown, 
crisp & flaky pastries, studded with a constellation of melty, chocolatey Chips. You'll find 8.5-ounce packages 
of eight, Trader Joe's Mini Chocolate Chip Croissant Swirls in our freezers, every day.

Mini Chocolate Chip Croissant Swirls

title: Dulce de Leche Ice Cream
description:
While some desserts are awesomely ornate in their construction, dulce de leche is sublimely simple: on the most 
fundamental level, all it requires to make is milk, sugar, and the patience to let it slowly simmer until it thickens 
to a caramelized texture, color, and taste. And yet, despite its superlatively simple setup, dulce de leche has an 
undeniable depth of flavor, combining the richness of condensed milk with the sweetness of caramel. That's 
why we find it's an ideal flavor for our latest seasonal ice cream pint. In the spirit of such inspired simplicity, we 
invite you to enjoy this captivatingly creamy and caramelly Trader Joe's Dulce de Leche Ice Cream.

It's made especially for us by a trusted ice cream supplier, who starts with a base of creamy caramel ice cream, 
then adds a smooth, silky, and satisfyingly sweet swirl of milky, Dulce de Leche-style caramel. This double 
Dulce approach ensures that every spoonful is remarkably rich and full-flavored. And while we find that it 
more than stands on its own when enjoyed in a simple cup or cone, you may wish to take things to the next 
level by using it to make your own sundae, banana split, or milkshake. 

Dulce de Leche Ice Cream

title: Japanese Style Fried Rice
description:
What exactly is Trader Joe's Japanese Style Fried Rice? It's a big favorite among our Crew Members, and a 
mainstay in our freezer case. More specifically, it's our take on takikomi gohan, a traditional Japanese style of 
rice flavored with soy sauce and mirin (a tangy rice wine). Our version contains shelled edamame, pieces of 
deep fried tofu, and thin strips of hijiki seaweed. What's inside the package you'll find in our freezers is fully 
cooked-you can heat it in minutes in a microwave or skillet or wok-and works brilliantly as either a side with 
a larger Japanese-inspired meal or as the main dish for a vegetarian feast. You could also go the fusion route and 
serve it topped with Sriracha and a fried egg. (#putaneggonit) You'll find it alongside the other fried rice options 
in our freezers-we're selling each 16-ounce bag for $2.99, every day.

title: Breaded Mozzarella Cheese Sticks
description:
Trader Joe's Breaded 
Mozzarella Cheese Sticks begin 
with part skim mozzarella 
cheese from Wisconsin. This 
family owned cheese company 
specifically uses rbst free 
cheese for our sticks. We 
developed a panko breading 
seasoned with garlic that bakes 
up in less than 10 minutes.  
There just enough breading that 
doesn't overpower the cheese. 
 
We are selling 16 oz. bag of 
Trader Joe's Breaded 
Mozzarella Sticks for $3.99.

title: Korean Style Beef Short Ribs
description:
Here's a quick dinner idea we think will really excite you! Trader Joe's Korean Style Beef Short Ribs. It's a 
simple entrée, really - lean beef short ribs marinated in a Korean style sweet and savory soy-based marinade. 
In the marinade, soy sauce and garlic account for the Ribs savory flavors, then brown sugar is added to make 
it deliciously sweet. The combination is simple, yet phenomenal. 

The genius is really in the preparation, and that's where you come in. In about 15 minutes (if you count the 
time it takes to thaw the meat), these simple Short Ribs cook to utter perfection - just pop them on a grill 
- or grill pan on the stovetop - at medium-high heat, cook for a couple of minutes on each side and, you're 
done. See? Genius! Before devouring, the Beef should be cooked thoroughly, at 160 degrees Fahrenheit or 
higher measured by a food thermometer. You'll find each 20-ounce package of Korean Style Beef Short Ribs 
containing five short ribs in our freezers.

 *Please check QIL to confirm current 

Korean Style Beef Short Ribs
tags: ["Alfresco Dining","Crack a Beer","Dinner Hack","Fire Up The Grill","Game Night","In Lieu of Pizza"]

title: Hot & Spicy Chicken Wings
description:
It wasn't that long ago that the wings of a chicken were regarded as parts to be discarded. But, in an 
unexpected turnover, the chicken wing has intercepted the top spot for beloved bar nosh and ubiquitous 
sports-watching snacks. Now, Trader Joe's brings our own version of wings to the table (or bar top). Our new 
Hot & Spicy Chicken Wings have a list of stats that will make it hard-if not impossible-to catch a game 
without wanting them close-at-hand. 

Here's what makes our Wings soar above local pub grub: First, they come from vegetarian chickens. That 
means our California-grown birds are raised on a balanced diet of corn and soybean meal. They are never 
fed animal fat or animal by-products. Second, our Wings are 100% antibiotic-free (ABF). This is especially 
notable, since Trader Joe's is currently the only retailer selling completely ABF, hot and spicy wings. Third, our 
Wings are super easy to prepare. They've been fully cooked and promptly frozen. This means they're ready to 
heat at a moment's notice, in the microwave or conventional oven.

Like the original Buffalo wings, ours are "sectioned" (cut in half), and covered in a spicy sauce made from 
vinegar, cayenne peppers, and chile pepper extract. These bite- (or three) sized snacks are the perfect finger-
food. Spray canola oil on your baking tray for extra-crispy wings. And, be sure to have some cool dip at the 
ready. Try our Low-Fat Parmesan Ranch [sku 17784], or our Greek Style Feta Dressing [sku 93244] as the 
perfect foil for the spicy, vinegary sauce-with a handful of Cut & Peeled Baby Carrots [sku 70588] on the side.

Each 16-ounce (1-pound) bag of our Hot & Spicy Chicken Wings is $5.99. Move some down the field-from 
our freezer to yours-and you'll be primed for the next big game!

11.10.
14
tags: ["Alfresco Dining","Crack a Beer","Effortless Entertaining","Finger Food","Game Night","Mouth On Fire","Picnic"]

title: Chiles Rellenos con Queso
description:
A much-beloved mainstay of Mexican cuisine, the chile relleno is a masterclass of complementary flavors and 
textures: each bite manages to combine the gooeyness of melted cheese, the tenderness of a fire-roasted pepper, 
and the crispiness of its egg-battered exterior, all at once. Of course, a dish with such a delightfully complex 
eating experience usually results from an equally complex cooking experience, and one doesn't always have the 
time to fire-roast, stuff, batter, and fry a whole pepper. That's what makes Trader Joe's Chiles Rellenos Con 
Queso so convenient-now, having a hearty chile relleno at home is simply a matter of letting it cook in the 
microwave, air fryer, or conventional oven, heating the included zesty tomato sauce on the stove or microwave, 
combining, and enjoying.

An always-excellent entrée or appetizer, our frozen Chiles Rellenos make an especially great vegetarian option 
for a weeknight dinner or weekend lunch. For a quick and easy meal, try pairing them with a side of rice and 
beans, which will also help soak up the rich and flavorful sauce. Of course, if you're feeling extra hungry, you 
can always use one as the filling for a super satisfying burrito, along with some diced tomatoes, onions, and our 
Organic Chunky Homestyle Guacamole [sku 71498].

Chiles Rellenos con Queso

title: Papas Rellenas
description:
An essential element of countless cuisines across Latin America and the Caribbean, the papa rellena might just 
be the ideal comfort food. While exact recipes vary, region to region, they're typically made by stuffing savory-
seasoned ground beef into a ball of mashed potatoes, which is then rolled in breadcrumbs and fried until 
it's crispy, golden brown, and mouthwateringly delicious. On paper, it sounds a little like a spicier, appetizer 
version of a shepherd's pie. As Trader Joe's Papas Rellenas ably demonstrate, on the palate, it's so much more. 

Drawing inspiration from the Cuban variation of this classic, comfy croquette, Trader Joe's Papas Rellenas are 
made with a picadillo-esque filling of ground beef, diced onions and bell peppers, along with a lively blend of 
herbs and seasonings like garlic, oregano, and black pepper. Each package contains four Papas Rellenas, which 
crisp up beautifully in either the conventional oven or the air fryer, after which they're ready to be enjoyed as 
an hors d'oeuvre, snack, or side, with a tart, creamy, or spicy dipping sauce. Or, if you prefer, they also make an 
excellent entrée-prepare a few Papas Rellenas per person, then serve on a plate with Spanish Style Rice [sku 
73936], Organic Black Beans [sku 50262], and your favorite TJ's salad kit. 

Papas Rellenas
tags: ["Dinner Hack","Fry It Up","In Lieu of Pizza"]

title: Spicy Meat Pizza
description:
Meat lovers, rejoice-it's time to meet-za the pizza of your dreams! Made for us in Italy by one of our favorite 
pizza partners, Trader Joe's Spicy Meat Pizza starts like all good pizzas do: with high-quality dough. Our 
supplier leaves the dough to proof for a full 24 hours, then hand-stretches it into roughly 10-inch crusts. Each 
crust is then topped with an umami-rich tomato sauce (made with a bit of Balsamic vinegar to deepen its 
flavor), shredded mozzarella cheese, and a top-tier trio of tasty toppings: spicy smoked sausage, savory pork 
meatballs, and grilled red bell peppers. 

The Calabrian-recipe sausage is arguably the star of the show here. It eats a bit like an Italian chorizo and 
really brings chili-pepper heat; the meatballs add even more umami, and the grilled bell peppers lend some 
sweetness to this pleasantly balanced pie. All told, TJ's Spicy Meat Pizza is the kind of simple yet elegant 
pie you'd find at a charming Italian pizzeria¿ except you'll find this Pizza pie in the freezers, only at your 
neighborhood Trader Joe's. 

Spicy Meat Pizza
tags: ["Alfresco Dining","Crack a Beer","Dinner Hack","Game Night","Mouth On Fire"]

title: Chocolate Hold the Cone! Mini Ice Cream Cones
description:
When we first introduced our Hold the Cone! Mini Ice Cream Cones back in 2011 [skus 95433 & 95434], they 
were an instant hit with our customers. Who could resist these adorably miniature and satisfyingly indulgent 
little Cones? Very few, it seemed. Very few. But at Trader Joe's, we are always interested in improving upon a good 
thing-so last year, our buyer set out to see if we could "build a better cone," as it were. As it would turn out, we 
could. And we did.

Our new Hold the Cone! Mini Ice Cream Cones begin with a crispier, crunchier cone, lined with fine European-
sourced and U.S.-made chocolate; the chocolate is notably richer and more flavorful than in our previous 
incarnation. Next, these mini, chocolate-lined treasures are piped full of thick, creamy Chocolate ice cream. The 
Ice Cream our new vendor makes is so deliciously dense because it contains only around 50% overrun (that's ice 
cream lingo for the amount of air whipped into the ice cream to expand its volume), which is impressive when 
you consider that most ice cream used in frozen novelties contains around 90% overrun. Finally, the Cones are 
dipped-upside down, no less!-in more of that fine, fine chocolate. 

Snatch a Mini Cone (or three) out of the freezer whenever your sweet tooth calls-at under 100 calories each, they 
are easily worth the indulgence. If you're in the mood to share, serve these Mini Ice Cream Cones at parties-
they're perfect for a simple-but-highly-Instagram-able baby shower, birthday party, graduation banquet, etc. 
Plus, they're an incredible value. We've increased the overall weight of the product by a third (from 5.9 to 7.89 
ounces, to be exact), but we haven't increased the price-each box of 8 Mini Chocolate Ice Cream Cones is still 
just $2.99. You'll find them along with their Vanilla [sku 57185] counterparts in our freezers. 

05.22.
17

title: 4 Almond Croissants
description:
Getting right to the point, and throwing modesty out the window, Trader Joe's 4 Almond Croissants are 
extraordinary. We thought it would be a bit presumptuous to put "extraordinary" on the label, though we think 
you'll agree that they're extraordinary on every level. To begin, while they require a soupçon of forethought, 
they're super-simple. Just remove from the package, place on a baking sheet and thaw overnight. They'll rise as 
they thaw - for the uninitiated, this is "proofing." When you wake in the morning, simply bake them in your 
oven for about 20 minutes. The dough is buttery and bakes to a crispy-on-the-outside, flaky-chewy on the 
inside finish. They're filled with sweet almond paste and topped with almond flakes. In other words, if you're 
an almond lover, you're in for a real treat! 

Freshly baked almond croissants of this quality might cost you $5-$6 each in a bakery. Or you could order 
a mail order version and spend a week's salary (only kind of joking). Or you could buy a box of 4 Almond 
Croissants at Trader Joe's for about what you'd pay for a single bakery croissant. You'll find them in our freezers.

4 Almond Croissants
tags: ["Alfresco Dining","Brunch All Day","Feeling Fancy","Let's Bake!","Rise & Shine"]

title: 4 Chocolate Croissants
description:
Like their carb cousins the brioche and Danish pastry, croissants belong to a family of baked goods collectively 
referred to as viennoiseries, baked goods made with yeast-leavened, laminated dough that's enriched with eggs, 
butter, or milk. They first arrived in France by way of Austria in the late 1800's, and are now ubiquitous in French 
bakery culture, their glossy, flaky crust and tender crumb a mainstay of breakfast and snacktime. While flavor 
variations run the gamut from sweet to savory, the pain au chocolat, or chocolate croissant, is the preferred 
variation of many a pastry connoisseur-this is just one of the many reasons why Trader Joe's Chocolate 
Croissants have become a mainstay of our frozen cases.

Made with creamy butter and filled with rich, semisweet Belgian chocolate, Trader Joe's Chocolate Croissants 
bring high-end bakery quality to your home kitchen with minimal effort. Remove them from the package and 
let them proof overnight (just as a French bakery would); in the morning you'll find the Croissants have nearly 
tripled in size! Brush with an egg wash, then bake 20-25 minutes until the Croissants are a deep golden brown. 
Let them rest for 10 minutes (distract yourself by brewing a pot of TJ's French Vanilla Coffee [sku 51484]), and 
then prepare to delight in the gooey melted Chocolate and warm, flaky Croissant dough. Yummmmm. 

Each 12-ounce box contains four ready-to-proof-and-bake Chocolate Croissants, so you can bake a bunch for 
brunch, or savor them one by one as a weekday breakfast or snack. You'll find them in the freezer cases at your 
neighborhood Trader Joe's, for $4.49 per box.
tags: ["Alfresco Dining","Brunch All Day","Feeling Fancy","Let's Bake!","Stuff of Dreams","Treat Yourself"]

title: Vegetable Bird's Nests
description:
Perhaps you've heard of those edible bird's nests that are a delicacy in parts of Asia. Aside from being cost 
prohibitive (they can be up to $3,000 per pound!), and also being difficult to procure in the States, the idea of 
eating an actual nest constructed by birds is not all that palatable to most eaters outside those cultures. But what 
about the idea of "nests" made of vegetables?

Trader Joe's Vegetable Bird's Nests are indeed popular wtihin the Customer culture of TJ's. We've offered 
them since 2003! Vegetable Bird's Nests are a combination of julienned onions and carrots with chopped kale 
that have been loosely woven together and then fried in tempura batter. Once you reheat these fully cooked 
Nests from frozen (in the conventional oven or with a quick re-fry in oil), you'll have an artistic appetizer to 
pair with other Asian flavors. Enjoy their crisp crunch and dip them in the included, soy-based sauce if you 
like! Find them in our freezers every day.

 *Please check QIL to confirm current pricing.

Vegetable Bird's Nests
tags: ["Alfresco Dining","Effortless Entertaining","Fry It Up","Game Night","Midday Snacks","The \"X\" Factor"]

title: Steamed Chicken Soup Dumplings
description:
Soup goes in a bowl or in a cup-unless, of course, you are a fan of Xiao Long Bao. Then, your soup goes in a 
dumpling. Trader Joe's Steamed Chicken Soup Dumplings are a wonder to behold, both for their display of 
Chinese food innovation, and for their incredibly comforting flavor profile. 

This concept originates in the Jiangnan region of southeastern China, where Shanghai is situated. Xiao Long 
Bao are essentially soup dumplings, but instead of dumplings that go in the soup (though you can still certainly 
make this happen), the soup actually goes inside these dumplings. Our expert Chinese dumpling supplier forms 
their wheat flour dumpling dough with a specially formulated proprietary production method that seals each 
dumpling, allowing them to hold the maximum amount of savory broth-broth made from ingredients includ-
ing chicken, onion, green onion, soy sauce, and ginger. Once the soup is wrapped in the dough and sealed (Bao 
means "wrapped" in Chinese), it is steamed until fully cooked (Xiao Long refers to a traditional Chinese bamboo 
steamer). Lastly, our dumplings are put into microwave-safe packages and frozen so we can deliver them to you.

To enjoy, you simply cut the corner of the bag and microwave for 1 to 2 minutes. Let your Dumplings sit for at 
least another minute before removing from microwave. The insides will be very hot, so be careful! We suggest 
placing a hot Soup Dumpling on a deep Chinese soup spoon and nibbling a little hole in the side to let the soup 
run out before enjoying soup and dumpling together.

You get six large Chicken Soup Dumplings in each six ounce package for $2.99. With Trader Joe's, the soup's 
not only on-it's IN! ¿ in our Dumplings and in our freezers, everyday.

10.14.
15
tags: ["Chance of Rain","Cold Front","Dinner Hack","In Lieu of Pizza","Rain or Shine"]

title: Organic Roasted Vegetable Pizza
description:
You've been told to "Eat your vegetables," as long as you can remember¿ and as long as you can remember, 
you've bristled at the thought. Now, our Organic Roasted Vegetable Pizza is here to help change all that! 

Trader Giotto's Organic Roasted Vegetable Pizza is loaded with roasted eggplant, zucchini, red onion, grilled 
yellow and red peppers, and garlic. By "roasted," we don't mean they were briefly passed over a flame to make 
them look charred. Our supplier near Bologna, Italy has really roasted these vegetables until they achieved their 
inviting look and taste. And rather than dicing them, they've chopped these veggies in longer strips to provide 
more textural interest for your tongue and the more distinguishable flavor from bite to bite. These colorful, plen-
tiful vegetables sit atop a crisp and chewy sourdough crust (made from a long-rise dough) that is spread with a 
well-seasoned tomato sauce and sprinkled with a blend of mozzarella and hard aged cheese. The taste-experience 
alone is enough to make you forget about pepperoni-at least for a few minutes. 

In addition to the great flavor-combination, this pizza really stands out for its Organic attribute. There are 
many frozen pizzas on the market that claim to be "made with some organic ingredients," but very few that are 
like ours. From dough to sauce to cheese to veggies, Trader Giotto's Roasted Vegetable Pizza is wholly Or-
ganic-100%. 

This frozen pie bakes up in your 425ºF oven in just 12-15 minutes at a cost that, like our ingredients, includes 
no unnecessary additives. $4.49 puts this 16.08-ounce Organic Roasted Vegetable Pizza in your hands-and 
shortly thereafter, in your mouth. So go ahead... Eat your vegetables!

10.05.
15
tags: ["Alfresco Dining","Crack a Beer","Dinner Hack","Game Night","Rain or Shine"]

title: Spaghetti Carbonara
description:
Within the vast continuum of comfort foods, pasta dishes are often among the most comforting. And within 
that subset of comfort foods, carbonara may just be the queen. Rich, creamy, and satisfying, with plenty of 
savory cheese and smoky pancetta (do we really need to say any more after that?), a great carbonara can lift 
moods, nourish spirits, and leave one feeling consummately cozy and content. Brought to us by a supplier in 
Italy, Trader Joe's Spaghetti Carbonara is, indeed, a great carbonara, made even greater by its remarkable 
value and effortless method of preparation.

Once brought home, from our freezers into yours, all this Carbonara needs is a few minutes in the microwave  
or stovetop before it's steamy, creamy, and enchantingly aromatic. Every forkful is full-flavored and luxuriously 
textured, from the al dente bite of the spaghetti to the savoriness of the egg, Grana Padano, and Pecorino 
Romano-based sauce, to the toothsomeness of the tender, diced pancetta. It makes an excellent (not to mention 
effortless) dinner option, whether it's enjoyed as a well planned out feast with garlic bread, stuffed mushrooms, 
and grilled zucchini, or a last-minute meal combined with one of our super quick salad kits.

Spaghetti Carbonara
tags: ["Dinner Hack","Gild The Lily","In Lieu of Pizza","Pair With Wine"]

title: French Vanilla Ice Cream
description:
Trader Joe's French Vanilla Ice Cream is a super premium vanilla ice cream that talks the talk - we don't mean French; 
we mean the language of flavor! Our rich French Vanilla Ice Cream has an unmistakably creamy-custard texture that 
can be enjoyed plain or used as a companion for any combination of cookies, candies, and chocolates.

What makes a quart of French vanilla ice cream "French", you ask? It has nothing to do with the vanilla bean itself 
(which is only grown near the equator, not near France at all); it merely means that the ice cream begins with a base 
that contains egg yolks, unlike regular vanilla ice cream. Trader Joe's French Vanilla Ice Cream is made in this French 
tradition, which ultimately lends a pale-yellow color and a richer, smoother consistency than traditional vanilla ice cream.  
Notice that super premium designation? To get there, an ice cream must have less than 50% overrun, meaning that one 
gallon of mix would create no more than one and a half gallons of finished ice cream. Trader Joe's French Vanilla Ice 
Cream has 26% overrun - aka dense, super SUPER premium ice cream! We're selling each one quart container of French 
Vanilla Ice Cream for $3.99*. Find it in our freezers and fill your favorite cone today!

 *Please Check QIL to confirm current pricing

French Vanilla Ice Cream

title: Calamansi & Mango Sorbet
description:
Drawing inspiration from two fundamental fruits within the culinary canon of the Philippines, Trader Joe's 
Calamansi & Mango Sorbet is a tangy, velvety, and remarkably refreshing frozen dessert (that just happens to 
be totally vegan). Combining the bracingly bright and tart tones of Calamansi (a lime-like citrus fruit native 
to the Philippines) with the lush, tropical flavors of Mango (the national fruit of the Philippines, no less!), each 
spoonful of this seasonal Sorbet is beautifully balanced between its sweet and sour elements. 

Give Trader Joe's Calamansi & Mango Sorbet a try as a palate-cleanser between bites of a creamy brie or blue 
cheese on a charcuterie board. Savor it as a dessert after a hearty meal of well-seasoned Salmon [sku 24455] 
and Shishito Peppers [sku 54163]. Or just enjoy it by the pint-ful, while watching a movie or catching up on 
your shows. Whatever you do, be sure to pick some up soon-supply is limited, and at this price, it's sure to go 
quite quickly.

Calamansi & Mango Sorbet

title: Chocolate Cheesecake Bites
description:
What's better than a bite of chocolate cheesecake? How about twelve bites of chocolate cheesecake? Or, rather, 
twelve Trader Joe's Chocolate Cheesecake Bites! Picture a dozen party-sized squares of tangy, velvety, 
chocolate chip-studded cheesecake, perched atop rich, extra-chocolatey crumble crust. Doesn't that sound 
dreamy? We think so. Don't take our word for it-biting is believing. 

Our Chocolate Cheesecake Bites are enticingly edible after just a two-hour thaw at room temperature (slightly 
longer if you opt to thaw them in the refrigerator), making them an easy way to wow your Valentine when 
baking isn't in the cards. Share them with twelve friends... or six hungry friends... or one, super-hungry, you! 
You'll find our Chocolate Cheesecake Bites in our freezers, for a limited time only.

Chocolate Cheesecake Bites

title: Creamy Spinach & Artichoke Dip
description:
This dip has the ideal blend of 'chokes and spinach, with Swiss and Parmesan cheeses, and just the right 
combination of herbs and spices. It's homey enough to serve with tortilla chips and salsa while watching a 
ball game, and impressive enough to present with baguette slices and apples at a dinner party. Getting back 
to that whole "outside the box" thing, we humbly suggest spreading Trader Joe's Spinach & Artichoke Dip 
on a burger, paired with shredded cheese for an amped-up quesadilla, or as a sauce on steamed broccoli or 
cauliflower - memorable and monumental dinner options, without a monumental amount of effort. Versatile, 
delicious and incredibly convenient - a winning combination if we do say so ourselves. 

We're selling each 8.8 ounce package of Spinach & Artichoke Dip for $2.99* - you'll find it in our freezers.

 *Please check QIL to confirm current pricing.

Spinach & Artichoke Dip

title: Sea Scallops
description:
-Dry 10/20 scallops per lb   
-Hand Shucked at Sea and individually quick frozen  
-Chemical Free  
-Caught in the cold US waters of the Atlantic Ocean  
-No pieces, only whole scallops  
 
DID you know? 

¿ Harvesting Scallops improves the overall scallop bed's health. Some of these beds are 6-  
15 feet deep with scallops, and harvesting the top layers allows the lower layers to thrive. 

¿ Scallops are carefully regulated- landings are monitored by the National Marine Fisheries 
Service. Each Scallop boat has a GPS tracker to ensure compliance. 

¿ Scallop beds are monitored by the government ensuring little by catch. 
¿ Our scallops are harvested with sea turtle friendly equipment
tags: ["Alfresco Dining","Date Night","Feeling Fancy","Fry It Up","In Lieu of Pizza","Pair With Wine"]

title: Kanom Krok Thai Coconut Pancakes
description:
Thai coconut-rice pancakes, or kanom krok, are among the most popular street foods in Thailand. If you've 
been fortunate enough to visit Thailand and try one (or several) of these dome-shaped, two-bite-sized treats for 
yourself, you can certainly understand why. And even if your travels haven't yet taken you to Thailand, you're 
in luck, because Trader Joe's Thai Coconut Pancakes are bringing this delicacy straight to your freezer! 

Following an authentic recipe, Trader Joe's Thai Coconut Pancakes are made for us in Thailand from a simple, 
straightforward batter of coconut milk, rice flour, cane & coconut sugars, tapioca starch, rice bran oil, and a 
bit of sea salt. Our supplier pours the batter into an indented pan (think muffin-tin-meets-cast-iron-deviled-
egg-plate), adds some shredded young coconut and taro root, then bakes it until the Pancakes are crisp on the 
outside and custardy on the inside. Preparation on your end couldn't be easier: simply remove the Pancakes' 
packaging, heat them in an air-fryer for 7-8 minutes (or  in the microwave for 50-60 seconds), and enjoy a 
sweet & salty taste of Thailand.

Thai Coconut Pancakes

title: Jalapeño & Cream Cheese Crispy Wontons
description:
There's a whole wide world of appetizers out there; some are creamy and cheesy, some are crispy and crunchy, 
and some are hot and spicy. And some, like Trader Joe's Jalapeño & Cream Cheese Crispy Wontons, manage 
to be all of those at once-and more! They're made with a marvelously rich mix of tangy cream cheese, savory 
Parmesan, and diced jalapeño, which is then wrapped in a wonton skin and fried until bubbly and golden 
brown. A little like a mix between a rangoon and jalapeño popper, every bite of these captivatingly Crispy 
Wontons is superbly savory, pleasantly spicy, and most of all, totally satisfying.

No need to bring out the deep fryer or heat a whole pot of oil, either: these Wontons go from frozen to crispy 
and delicious in just about 10 minutes in a conventional oven, or a little more than half that in an air fryer. 
Once cooked, they're ready to be served for all kinds of occasions: try them as an easy starter for a quick stir-
fry dinner, an hors d'oeuvre for a cocktail night with friends, or as a super flavorful snack when folks for over 
for the big game. Wherever and whenever you have them, just be sure to pair them with a bit of our Sweet Chili 
Sauce [sku 91113], for dipping.

Jalapeño & Cream Cheese
Crispy Wontons

title: Garlic Shiitake Green Beans
description:
Side-dish ideas are sometimes put on the back burner while we spend the majority of our menu-planning 
on main dishes. Thankfully, your neighborhood Trader Joe's offers scores of sides that are both delicious and 
ready to enjoy in just minutes-no planning required. Trader Joe's Garlic Shiitake Green Beans is an excellent 
example.

Our supplier in Thailand, who also makes our Lightly Salted Edamame [sku 51063], knows a thing or two 
about preparing high-quality, frozen legumes. In this case, they start with Thai-grown green beans, par-cook 
them, and season them with a seriously umami-licious, soy-based sauce that's amped up with garlic & shiitake 
mushrooms. The dish is flash-frozen, packaged, and delivered to our stores, where you can pick it up any day 
of the week. 

Getting these Garlic Shiitake Green Beans ready for their supporting supper role is a swift, five-minute affair. 
It requires just a quick sauté & steam on the stovetop-or a handful of microwave minutes. The still-firm beans, 
with their garlic-forward flavor and delicious mushroom undertones, pair well with Trader Joe's Beef Bulgogi 
[sku 75283] and your favorite TJ's rice... but there are many more mains that would be happy to call this savory 
bean dish their sidekick!

Garlic Shiitake Green Beans
